The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma The third edition of the Glam Awards is set to take place in Zvishavane next Saturday with event organisers appealing for sponsorship. Founded in 2016 by MSU student Takudzwa Chigiya, the awards are meant to expose artistes at grassroots level. Said Chigiya: “After a successful ceremony in Gweru last year, this year’s event will be held in Zvishavane. We’ve started preparing for the event and we are appealing for sponsorship. He said the awards are meant to recognise the up-and-coming artistes’ hard work. Those interested in sponsoring the event, Chigiya said, can contact them via their website or through their Facebook page. Chigiya said the nominees would be released sometime this week. — @mthabisi_mthire